==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Transmew
<hw>Trans*mew"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t. & i.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>transmuer</ets>, L. <ets>transmutare</ets>. See
<er>Transmute</er>.]</ety> <def>To transmute; to transform; to
metamorphose.</def> <mark>[Archaic]</mark> <rj><au>Chaucer.
Spenser.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>To <qex>transmew</qex> thyself from a holy hermit into a sinful
forester.</q> <rj><qau>Sir W. Scott.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Transmigrant</ent>⟦br⟧
